The charters in this collection, given on the authority of these authentia materiale, are distinguished from those taken from either of the Registers‚ by being printed with the abbreviations of the originals. They are also indicated in the prefixed Table.

Fac-similes of original charters of King Williarn and King Malcolm IV. are inserted as fair specimens of the charter hand of the different periods. Another fac-simile has been given for a different reason. It is an indenture of lease, for a term of 30 years from 1312, between the Convent and the Hays of Leys, containing minute stipulations which were of great importance to the parties, and which being in Latin, required explanation for the unlearned, whether clerk or layman.
